# Mintlify Workflow

## 1 — Architecture

### Repository Strategy

Mintlify docs live in a **separate repo** from ZajalyDocs. This is intentional:

| Repo | Purpose | Platform |
|---|---|---|
| `rovony/ZajalyDocs` | Obsidian vault + GitBook sync | GitBook |
| `rovony/ZajalyDocs_Mintlify` | Mintlify-specific MDX + docs.json | Mintlify |

Mintlify auto-deploys on every push to the default branch. No build commands needed.

### Published URLs

| Project | Default URL | Custom Domain |
|---|---|---|
| Zajaly Dev Docs | `zajalydocs-mintlify.mintlify.app` | `docs.zajaly.dev` |

Additional product docs can be separate Mintlify projects (each gets free custom domain) or tabs within one project.

### Required Files

Every Mintlify project must contain:

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `docs.json` | Central config — navigation, theme, colors, integrations |
| `index.mdx` | Home page |
| `favicon.svg` | Site favicon |
| `logo/light.png` | Logo for light mode |
| `logo/dark.png` | Logo for dark mode |

