### Config File — Critical Note

Mintlify migrated from `mint.json` to `docs.json` in early 2025. If you see `mint.json` in old tutorials, it's outdated. Always use `docs.json`. Run `mint upgrade` to auto-convert `mint.json` to `docs.json`.

### CLI Reference

**Prerequisite:** Node.js v20.17.0+ (LTS recommended), Git installed.

```bash
npm i -g mint          # Install CLI globally
mint dev               # Local preview at localhost:3000
mint dev --port 3333   # Custom port
mint update            # Update CLI to latest version
```

Additional commands:

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `mint new [dir]` | Scaffold a new Mintlify project (starter kit) |
| `mint broken-links` | Find broken internal links (`--check-anchors` for anchor links) |
| `mint a11y` | Check accessibility (color contrast, missing alt text) |
| `mint validate` | Validate build in strict mode (for CI/CD pipelines) |
| `mint openapi-check <file>` | Validate an OpenAPI spec file or URL |
| `mint rename <old> <new>` | Rename a file and update all references |
| `mint migrate-mdx` | Convert MDX endpoint pages to OpenAPI auto-generated pages |
| `mint upgrade` | Convert `mint.json` to `docs.json` |

Flags for `mint dev`: `--port`, `--disable-openapi` (skip OpenAPI processing), `--groups [name]` (preview as auth group).

