## 2 — Writing Mintlify-Compatible MDX

### File Format

Mintlify uses MDX — Markdown with JSX components. Use `.mdx` extension (`.md` works but limits component usage).

### Frontmatter (Required)

Every page must begin with YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Clear, specific, keyword-rich title"
description: "Concise description for SEO and page metadata (under 160 chars)"
---
```

Additional optional frontmatter fields:

```yaml
---
title: "Page Title"
description: "Brief description"
sidebarTitle: "Short Sidebar Title"
icon: "book"
tag: "NEW"
mode: "wide"
hidden: true
noindex: true
keywords: ['configuration', 'setup']
---
```

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `title` | Page title in navigation and browser tabs |
| `description` | SEO meta description, displays under the title |
| `sidebarTitle` | Shorter title for sidebar navigation |
| `icon` | Icon next to page title (Lucide, Font Awesome, or Tabler name) |
| `tag` | Badge next to page title in sidebar (e.g., "NEW", "BETA") |
| `mode` | Page layout: `wide`, `custom`, `center`, `frame` (omit for default) |
| `hidden` | Remove from sidebar; still accessible via URL |
| `noindex` | Prevent search engine indexing |
| `keywords` | Internal search keywords (not visible on page) |

### Standard Markdown

All standard markdown works: headings, paragraphs, lists, tables, code blocks, images, bold, italic, links.

### Links

Use relative paths without the `.mdx` extension:

- **Correct:** `[Quickstart](/quickstart)`
- **Wrong:** `[Quickstart](quickstart.mdx)`
- **Wrong:** `[[quickstart]]` (Obsidian wikilinks not supported)

### Code Blocks

Always specify language and optionally a filename:

````mdx
```bash install.sh
npm install @mintlify/cli
```
````

The filename appears as a title above the code block.

### Writing Style

- Use clear, direct language for technical audiences
- Write in second person ("you") for instructions
- Use active voice over passive voice
- Present tense for current states, future tense for outcomes
- Lead with the most important information (inverted pyramid)
- Break complex procedures into numbered steps
- Include expected outcomes after each major step
- Keep sentences concise while providing necessary context

