## 3 — Component Reference

Mintlify components are JSX tags used inside MDX files. Every opening tag must have a matching closing tag (or be self-closing).

### When to Use Which Component

| Component | Use When | Don't Use When |
|---|---|---|
| **Callouts** (Note/Warning/Tip/etc.) | Warnings, prerequisites, tips, success confirmations | Every other paragraph — overuse dilutes impact |
| **Steps** | Sequential procedure where order matters (install → configure → deploy) | Unordered options — use tabs instead |
| **Tabs** | Parallel alternatives (npm vs yarn, macOS vs Linux, cURL vs SDK) | Steps that must be done in sequence — use Steps |
| **CodeGroup** | Same concept in multiple languages (JS, Python, cURL) | Single code block — just use a plain fenced block |
| **Accordion** | Supplementary detail most readers can skip (troubleshooting, advanced config) | Critical information the reader needs |
| **Card** | Landing/overview pages linking to sections with descriptions | Inline navigation within a guide — use regular links |
| **Columns** | Side-by-side layout (2-4 cards, text beside image) | Long content unreadable in a narrow column |
| **Frame** | Images that need captions or visual framing | Plain inline images — use standard markdown `![alt](path)` |
| **ParamField / ResponseField** | API parameter and response documentation | Non-API content |
| **Tooltip** | Defining jargon or abbreviations inline | Full explanations — use a callout or paragraph instead |
| **Mermaid** | Flowcharts, sequence diagrams, ER diagrams | Simple lists or tables that don't need visual flow |
| **Badge** | Inline status labels ("NEW", "BETA", "Deprecated") | Page-level tags — use frontmatter `tag` instead |
| **Prompt** | Copyable AI prompts with Cursor integration | Non-AI content |

