## 5 — Navigation (docs.json)

The `navigation` property in `docs.json` controls sidebar and header navigation. Pages not listed in navigation are inaccessible (404).

### Required Root Fields

`docs.json` requires these four fields at minimum:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| `theme` | One of: `mint`, `maple`, `palm`, `willow`, `linden`, `almond`, `aspen`, `sequoia` |
| `name` | Project/product name |
| `colors.primary` | Hex color code (e.g., `#0A84FF`) |
| `navigation` | Navigation structure object |

### Minimal Structure

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://mintlify.com/docs.json",
  "theme": "mint",
  "name": "Zajaly Developer Docs",
  "colors": { "primary": "#0A84FF" },
  "navigation": {
    "groups": [
      {
        "group": "Getting Started",
        "pages": ["index", "quickstart"]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Navigation Elements

| Element | Purpose | Level |
|---|---|---|
| `pages` | Array of page file paths (without `.mdx`) | Leaf — the actual content |
| `groups` | Sidebar section headings | Organize pages into sections |
| `tabs` | Top-level horizontal navigation | Split docs into major areas |
| `anchors` | Persistent sidebar links | Quick access to key sections or external URLs |
| `dropdowns` | Expandable sidebar menu | Multi-section navigation |
| `products` | Product-specific navigation | Separate docs per product |
| `versions` | Version selector dropdown | API versioning |
| `languages` | Language selector dropdown | Internationalization |

### Groups with Icons and Tags

```json
{
  "group": "Writing Content",
  "icon": "notebook-text",
  "tag": "NEW",
  "pages": ["writing-content/page", "writing-content/text"]
}
```

### Nested Groups

```json
{
  "group": "Getting Started",
  "icon": "play",
  "pages": [
    "quickstart",
    {
      "group": "Advanced",
      "expanded": false,
      "pages": ["installation", "configuration"]
    }
  ]
}
```

`expanded: false` collapses nested groups by default.

### Group Root Page

Make a group title clickable:

```json
{
  "group": "API Pages",
  "root": "api-overview",
  "pages": ["api-reference/get", "api-reference/post"]
}
```

### Tabs (Major Sections)

```json
{
  "navigation": {
    "tabs": [
      {
        "tab": "Guides",
        "pages": ["index", "quickstart", "guides/overview"]
      },
      {
        "tab": "API Reference",
        "pages": ["api-reference/introduction"]
      },
      {
        "tab": "Blog",
        "href": "https://external-link.com/blog"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Products (Multi-Product Docs)

```json
{
  "navigation": {
    "products": [
      {
        "product": "Custojo",
        "icon": "users",
        "groups": [
          { "group": "Getting Started", "pages": ["custojo/quickstart"] },
          { "group": "Endpoints", "pages": ["custojo/api/users"] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "product": "Waraq",
        "icon": "code",
        "pages": ["waraq/overview"]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Global Navigation Elements

Elements under `navigation.global` appear across all pages/tabs/products:

```json
{
  "navigation": {
    "global": {
      "anchors": [
        { "anchor": "Blog", "icon": "newspaper", "href": "https://blog.zajaly.dev" }
      ],
      "tabs": [
        { "tab": "Changelog", "href": "/changelog" }
      ]
    },
    "groups": [...]
  }
}
```

Global `anchors`, `tabs`, `versions`, `languages`, `dropdowns`, and `products` all persist regardless of which section the user is viewing.

### OpenAPI in Navigation

```json
{
  "group": "API Reference",
  "openapi": "/api-reference/openapi.json",
  "pages": ["GET /users", "POST /users"]
}
```

Omit `pages` to auto-generate pages for all endpoints.

### When to Update docs.json

| Action | docs.json Change |
