## 6 — Writing Workflow (New Content)

Follow these steps when creating new Mintlify content:

1. **Identify the target.** Dev-facing docs go in the Mintlify repo (`rovony/ZajalyDocs_Mintlify`). Knowledge base content stays in ZajalyDocs.
2. **Check for existing content.** Search the repo for related pages before creating a new one.
3. **Create the `.mdx` file** in the correct subfolder. Include frontmatter with `title` and `description`.
4. **Write the content** using MDX with appropriate components (Steps for procedures, Tabs for alternatives, CodeGroup for multi-language, Cards for navigation).
5. **Follow writing standards:**
   - Lead with user goals, not system features
   - Include prerequisites before instructions
   - Add verification steps after major actions
   - Include troubleshooting for likely failure points
   - Write for scannability — headings, lists, white space
6. **Update `docs.json` navigation** — add the page to the correct group/tab.
7. **Test locally** — run `mint dev` and verify at localhost:3000.
8. **Verify** using the checklist in Section 7 below.

### Code Examples Standards

- Always include complete, runnable examples users can copy and execute
- Show proper error handling and edge cases
- Use realistic data instead of placeholder values
- Include expected outputs for verification
- Specify language and include filename when relevant
- Never include real API keys or secrets

### API Documentation Standards

- Document all parameters including optional ones
- Show both success and error response examples
- Include rate limiting information
- Provide authentication examples
- Explain all HTTP status codes
- Cover complete request/response cycles

### Accessibility Standards

- Include descriptive `alt` text for all images
- Use specific, actionable link text (never "click here")
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (start with H2 on pages, H1 is the page title)
- Use `<Frame>` with captions for important images
- Run `mint a11y` to check contrast ratios and missing alt text

### Editing Workflows

Three ways to edit Mintlify content:

| Method | Best For |
|---|---|
| **Code-based** (VS Code / Cursor) | Major restructuring, bulk edits, new pages. `mint dev` for local preview. |
| **Web editor** (dashboard.mintlify.com) | Quick typo fixes, content tweaks. Visual + Markdown modes, live preview, drag-and-drop navigation. |
| **Mintlify Agent** (Slack `@mintlify`) | AI-assisted doc updates from PRs, generate release notes, address review feedback. |

All three commit to the same Git repo. Use code-based for heavy work, web editor for light edits, agent for automation.

### Mintlify Agent Workflows (Pro)

The Mintlify agent (Slack or API) can:
- Update docs when merging feature PRs: `@mintlify Update docs for this PR: [link]`
- Generate release notes: `@mintlify Generate release notes for this PR: [link]`
- Generate code examples: `@mintlify Generate a code example for the auth flow`
- Review content: `@mintlify Review the API rate limiting section`
- API automation: `POST /api/agent/jobs` for CI/CD integration

