## 7 — Verification Checklist

Run through this after writing or editing any Mintlify content:

- [ ] **Frontmatter complete** — `title` and `description` present on every page
- [ ] **Navigation updated** — page listed in `docs.json` → `navigation` (unlisted pages return 404)
- [ ] **No broken links** — every linked page exists; paths use `/path` format without `.mdx`
- [ ] **Components matched** — every opening `<Component>` has a closing `</Component>`
- [ ] **Code blocks have language** — every fenced code block specifies a language
- [ ] **Images accessible** — all `<img>` and `<Frame>` elements have `alt` text
- [ ] **No wikilinks** — no `[[...]]` syntax (use `[text](/path)` format)
- [ ] **docs.json valid** — valid JSON, no trailing commas
- [ ] **Local preview works** — `mint dev` renders the page correctly at localhost:3000
- [ ] **API params documented** — all parameters (including optional) described with types

### Automated Verification Steps

When asked to verify Mintlify content:

1. **Link check:** Search for `[[` in all `.mdx` files — flag any wikilinks. Run `mint broken-links` for comprehensive link validation.
2. **Navigation sync:** List all `.mdx` files, compare against `docs.json` navigation — flag unlisted pages.
3. **Component matching:** Search for `<` tags and verify each opening tag has a closing tag or is self-closing.
4. **Frontmatter check:** Verify every `.mdx` file starts with `---` frontmatter containing `title` and `description`.
5. **docs.json validation:** Parse `docs.json` and check for JSON syntax errors. Run `mint validate` for strict build validation.
6. **Accessibility check:** Run `mint a11y` to detect contrast issues and missing alt text.

