## 10 — Mintlify vs GitBook — When to Use Which

| | **GitBook** | **Mintlify** |
|---|---|---|
| Best for | Knowledge base, guides, SOPs | API docs, developer-facing docs |
| File format | Markdown with `{% %}` blocks | MDX (Markdown + JSX components) |
| Config | `.gitbook.yaml` + `SUMMARY.md` | `docs.json` (single file) |
| API playground | No | Yes (built-in, interactive) |
| Custom domain | $65/mo | Free |
| Content source | ZajalyDocs monorepo (`rovony/ZajalyDocs`) | Separate repo (`rovony/ZajalyDocs_Mintlify`) |
| Deployment | Bidirectional Git Sync | Auto-deploy on push |
| Local preview | No | `mint dev` at localhost:3000 |
| CLI | None | `mint dev`, `mint update`, `mint validate`, `mint broken-links`, `mint a11y` |
| Components | Liquid-style `{% %}` tags | JSX components `<Component>` |
| Web editor | Yes (bidirectional sync) | Yes (visual + markdown modes, drag-and-drop nav) |
| AI agent | No | Slack `@mintlify` + API for automated doc updates (Pro) |
| Themes | No (single design) | 8 themes: mint, maple, palm, willow, linden, almond, aspen, sequoia |
| Redirects | `.gitbook.yaml` redirects section | `docs.json` redirects array (source/destination) |

Use GitBook for `ZajDocs/` knowledge base and `ZajProjects/` product overviews. Use Mintlify for `docs.zajaly.dev` developer-facing API documentation.
